An elementary school classroom needs a minimum of [`[$b]`] square feet for the teacher plus a minimum of [`[$r]`] square feet per student. So if there are [`n`] students, the total necessary area is [`[$left]`] square feet. If a classroom has [`[$total]`] square feet of area, then we have an inequality [`[$left]\leq[$right]\text{.}`] Could this classroom support [`[$proposed_solution]`] students?

